From eliot Subject Re Lexus and Infiniti In article A w TIGGER STCLOUD MSUS EDU writes First off, the correct spelling of Nissan's luxury automobile division is Infiniti not Infinity who cares about typos of these meaningless, synthetic names if the cars were named after a person, e g honda, i'd be more respectful Lexus GS V ES V SC V wrong the GS and SC use straight sixes, while the ES uses a V only a giant like toyota can afford to have both a V and inline in its lineup, but that won't last for long eliot